# Phase 6 Paddle billing example values
# VITE_PADDLE_CLIENT_TOKEN=test_...
# VITE_PADDLE_ENV=sandbox

# Server-side billing config for the repo-hosted backend
# APP_URL=http://localhost:5173
# PADDLE_API_KEY=pdl_sdbx_api_key_...
# PADDLE_NOTIFICATION_SECRET_KEY=pdl_ntfset_...
# PADDLE_PLUS_PRICE_ID=pri_...
# SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=sb_publishable_...
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=...

# Billing return behavior
# - The backend uses APP_URL as the shared billing landing page for Paddle checkout and entitlement refresh.
# - It appends ?billing=success, ?billing=cancel, or ?billing=portal automatically.
# - APP_URL also acts as the Paddle payment-link page by opening transactions from the _ptxn query param.
# - SUPABASE_URL / SUPABASE_ANON_KEY can be omitted on the server if the VITE_* variants are already present.

# Supabase redirect allowlist reminder for mobile/native Phase 5:
# - Web dev redirect: http://localhost:5173
# - Web prod redirect: your deployed app URL
# - Native callback (Android + iOS): com.generalmalit.myoreptimer://auth/callback

